Git - It is a tool for version control

version control - To keep track of a code 

Synchronise code - Syncing here means updating all the branches in the personal fork that are also present in the Host repository.
Ex: If 2 persons are working in the same project they will download the source code from the Host repository & work on it. 
After completing their part, they will commit into the Host repository.

This Host Repository is said to be GitHub.
The whole process is Git, The main server is GitHub. Note: we can also use other than GitHub like Gitlab, Bitbucket.
